CEO, Miracle Day Music, Omenka Uzoma Day has explained the motivation for his new song, Nigeria, saying it is special to him. In a chat with The Nation, Uzoma Day noted that the morals, culture, and unity in Nigeria have deteriorated compared to the days of the old.   Saidi Balogun, Ayo Adesanya feature in AK Media’s Extra Mile     Why I want to empower women, by Doris Nkumah     Razzy AG hints at collaboration with top music acts   He reminisced on growing up in a more united country devoid of insecurity and tribalism. He said: “This song Nigeria, I have lived in many countries but Nigeria is the headquarters of the black race all over the world. Our heritage is glorious. It is a country with grace, God is in Nigeria. Nigeria will unite again.” Continuing, he said, “This song Nigeria is to unite us. This song is for our youths. If we can put ourselves together and unite, Nigeria is the future of the world. I believe in Nigeria. I thank the minister of Arts and culture, the CEO, National Theatre for their support.”